Commentary Text: Chris Morris to Jofra Archer, out Lbw!! Fuller, yorker and gone. Archer took a review but in vain. Morris again has picked up a wicket. Four wickets for him today. Jofra Archer lbw b Chris Morris 2(3)

Commentary Text: Chahal to Samson, out Caught by Chris Morris!! Oh dear! Daft batting from Samson, he does this one so often - looks a million dollars one oment and then does such things. But full credit to Chahal, slowed down the pace - this one was bowled at 75 kmph, threw the leg-break wider and then spun away - Samson saw the loop and couldn't hold himself back, reached out for the lofted drive and skewed it off the base of the bat - high and down the throat of Morris at long-off. He's chuffed to bits and RCB are mounting a comeback. Samson c Chris Morris b Chahal 9(6) [6s-1]

Commentary Text: Chahal to Uthappa, out Caught by Finch!! That's the end of Uthappa's cameo - one shot too many and he eventually paid the price - nicely tossed up outside off, Uthappa went for the big slog-sweep, doesn't get anywhere near the middle of the bat, plenty of height, but not much in terms of distance. Commentary Text: Kartik Tyagi to Kohli, out Caught by Rahul Tewatia!! Tewatia pulls off a superb catch at the boundary. Third umpire is having a look at it, but Kohli has already started walking off. Absolutely brilliant from the man who was just coming off a wicket himself with his previous delivery. This is hit flat and hard as Kohli works his wrists across the line. It's travelling rapidly to the right of Tewatia at deep midwicket. He skirts along the edge of the boundary, takes it on his side with both hands and then tosses it up, giving himself enough time to run outside the boundary and then come back in for the rebound. Kohli c Rahul Tewatia b Kartik Tyagi 43(32) [4s-1 6s-2]

Commentary Text: Shreyas Gopal to Finch, out Caught by Uthappa!! Another case of Finch not converting his start. Gopal again, gets him for the second time in this tournament. Wonder, what spurs him to do so well when he plays against RCB. Always delivers. Nicely gives air, tempts Finch as he aims for the slog-sweep. Ends up slicing it up in the air off a top edge. Uthappa circles around from mid-on and makes no mistake. Finch c Uthappa b Shreyas Gopal 14(11) [6s-2]
